      {
        "id": "RA-M1-N2",
        "project": "libsass",
        "description": "Import entry and source file not deleted before exception throw, causing leak on recovery",
        "dispute_reason": "PR #3192 is still open (never merged). The exception thrown at L295 in register_resource() is caught inside sass_parse_block() (sass_context.cpp:L199, which has catch(...) + throw() specifier). The exception never escapes the C API boundary. sass_compile_context() unconditionally calls sass_delete_compiler() \u2192 ~Context(), and the destructor correctly frees both resources[] (loop-1) and import_stack[] (loop-2, via sass_import_take_source + sass_delete_import). The PR describes a hypothetical leak \"if client code captures and tries to recover from the exception\", but this scenario cannot occur through the C API. Defensive coding improvement, not an exploitable leak.",
        "repoaudit_detected": true,
        "speca_detected": false
      },
